{"title": "Missing sanitization of HTML template tags", "summary": "  Failing to sanitize user input can allow attackers to inject HTML tags (like `<script>` tags) into the rendered template. This can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks if the injected scripts are then executed.  Ensure user input is sanitized and, wherever possible, avoid rendering templates with raw user input. ", "description": "\n\nFailing to sanitize user input can allow attackers to inject HTML tags (like `<script>` tags)\ninto the rendered template. This can lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks if the injected\nscripts are then executed.\n\nEnsure user input is sanitized and, wherever possible, avoid rendering templates with raw user input.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u2705 Always sanitize user input before using it in a template\n\n```\n  safe := template.HTMLEscapeString(r.FormValue(\"xyz\"))\n```\n\n\u2705 Prefer html/template to text/template when parsing and rendering a template\n\n```go\n  import \"html/template\"\n\n  func good(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    t, _ = := template.New(\"something\").Parse(r.FormValue(\"xyz\"))\n    t.Execute(w, nil)\n  }\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-80"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/go_lang_missing_script_tag_sanitization"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}